<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued September 07 at 8:57PM MDT until September 07 at 9:30PM MDT by NWS Glasgow</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 930 PM MDT
FOR CENTRAL PHILLIPS COUNTY...
At 856 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 18 miles northeast
of Zortman, moving northeast at 45 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Malta, Zortman, Dodson, Fourchette, Phillips, Wagner, Landusky, Sun
Prairie and Fred Robinson Bridge.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...&lt;.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
